{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17586175","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17586175"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T08:27:11+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T08:27:11+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15069"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15069","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15069"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.45,0.15,0.25,0.05,0.1]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7757"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67782"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7757","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7757"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15069"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53247"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4933"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"8115"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"18935"},{"type":"contributions","id":"18938"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67782","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/67782"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003ERapidly progressive glomerulonephritis (RPGN) is characterised by rapid loss of kidney function. On kidney biopsy, crescentic formation is seen in the glomeruli.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes rapidly progressive glomerulonephritis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Progression from normal function to kidney failure occurs over weeks to months without treatment","Anti-glomerular basement membrane disease is Type II","Immune complex-mediated disease is Type III","Pauci-immune glomerulonephritis is Type I","Supportive care alone typically leads to complete recovery"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003ERPGN is a serious condition where \u003Cstrong\u003Eprogression from normal function to kidney failure occurs over weeks to months without treatment\u003C/strong\u003E. This rapid decline makes prompt diagnosis and treatment essential.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe classification of RPGN is as follows:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003EType I: Anti-glomerular basement membrane disease (including Goodpasture syndrome)\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EType II: Immune complex-mediated disease\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EType III: Pauci-immune glomerulonephritis\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAnti-glomerular basement membrane disease is Type II\u003C/strong\u003E - This is incorrect as it is Type I\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EImmune complex-mediated disease is Type III\u003C/strong\u003E - This is incorrect as it is Type II\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPauci-immune glomerulonephritis is Type I\u003C/strong\u003E - This is incorrect as it is Type III\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESupportive care alone typically leads to complete recovery\u003C/strong\u003E - This is incorrect as RPGN requires aggressive immunosuppressive therapy\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Rapidly progressive glomerulonephritis (RPGN) typically progresses from normal function to kidney failure over weeks to months without treatment","RPGN is classified into three types: Type I (anti-glomerular basement membrane), Type II (immune complex-mediated), and Type III (pauci-immune)","RPGN requires aggressive immunosuppressive therapy; supportive care alone is insufficient"],"references":["Rout P, Naik RH, Leslie SW. Rapidly Progressive Glomerulonephritis. 2024 Jun 7. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 32491362.","Moroni G, Ponticelli C. Rapidly progressive crescentic glomerulonephritis: Early treatment is a must. Autoimmun Rev. 2014 Jul;13(7):723-9. doi: 10.1016/j.autrev.2014.02.007. Epub 2014 Mar 19. PMID: 24657897.","Jennette, J. C., \u0026 D\u0027Agati, V. D. (2023). Heptinstall\u0027s Pathology of the Kidney. Lippincott Williams \u0026 Wilkins","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53247"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15069"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53247","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/53247"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-06T22:40:36+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-06T22:42:00+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7757"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67782"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"e